# The vendored googletest contains BUILD.bazel files referencing @rules_python and
# @com_google_absl, which are not in this Bzlmod graph. Without this entry,
# bazel query //... crawls into the directory and fails. The module is exposed to
# Bazel via local_path_override in MODULE.bazel instead.
libs/3rdparty/googletest

# The vendored ETL library ships its own upstream Bazel test tree (test/**) which
# references the library via root-relative labels (//:etl, //test/UnitTest++:...).
# Those labels only resolve when ETL is the workspace root (i.e. consumed as the
# @etl Bazel module). Vendored as source under this repo they do not resolve, so
# exclude ETL's own test packages from OpenBSW's Bazel build. ETL is built via
# libs/3rdparty/etl/BUILD.bazel (OpenBSW-owned, preserved through RIM 'ignores').
libs/3rdparty/etl/test
